Head 1.6 times as wide as long. Ocelli very large, located at level of posterior margins of eyes near occipital furrow, distance between ocelli about as long as distance between ocellus and posterior margin of eye. Apical segment of maxillary palp 1.3 times as long as preceding segment, gradually narrowed apicad from middle. Antenna moderately long, reaching one-fourth of elytral length when reclined; length × width of antennomeres (
holotype
): 1: 0.13 × 0.05; 2: 0.12 × 0.05; 3: 0.12 × 0.04; 4: 0.08 × 0.04; 5–6: 0.09 × 0.06; 7–10: 0.11 × 0.06; 11: 0.17 × 0.06.
